 policy for toxic wastes and governmental/corporate responsibility. Woburn, the authors predict, will become a code word for environmental struggles.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aHazardous wastesxEnvironmental aspectszMassachusettszWoburn. 0aLeukemia in childrenzMassachusettszWoburn. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Health Care Issues.2bisacsh  acancer clusters.  acancer.  acivic action.  aconservation.  acontaminated water.  acontamination.  acorporate responsibility.  acorporations.  adiseases.  aenvironment regulations.  aenvironmental impact.  aflint.  agroundwater.  ahealth policy.  ahealth.  alegal system.  aleukemia.  alitigation.  alove canal.  amassachusetts.  amedicine.  anature.  anonfiction.  apollution.  apopular science.  apublic health.  apublic policy.  asafe water.  ascience.  asustainability.  atoxic waste.  awater politics.  awater rights.  awoburn.1 aMikkelsen, Edwin J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052092048440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520920484423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520920484/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles